# User profile photos

User avatars live in `storage/Users/…` and are **not** public — always serve via `file.php`.

## Data model

| Layer | Location |
|---|---|
| File row | `s_yf_record_files` — `crm_record_id = vtiger_users.id`, `role = 'image'` |
| Legacy name | `vtiger_users.imagename` (display name of PNG) |
| FK | `s_yf_record_files.crm_record_id` → `vtiger_crmentity.crmid` (`fk_record_files_crmid`) |
| Disk | `storage/Users/{year}/{month}/week{n}/{userId}_{time}_{name}.png` (legacy prod blobs may use `{attachmentsid}_` prefix) |
| Sidecar | `{storage_path}.base64` — data-URI for mail/PDF (`getUserPhotoImgHtmlForGenerator()`) |

**Users module does not auto-create `vtiger_crmentity` rows.** Upload/insert into `s_yf_record_files` fails without `crmid = user id`, `setype = 'Users'`. Symptom: orphan blob in `storage/Users/` and/or empty `storage/Users/tmpfile{id}.tmp`, default icon in UI.

## Upload (`Users::uploadAndSaveFile`)

1. Validate image; delete prior avatar (`unlinkUserAvatarFilesForUserId`).
2. Save to `initStorageFileDirectory('Users')` + `{userId}_{time}_{sanitizedName}`.
3. Normalize via ImageMagick → **300×300 PNG** (`Users\Models\Record::normalizeUploadedUserPhotoFile`, `USER_PHOTO_SIZE`, `USER_PHOTO_MIME = image/png`).
4. Insert `s_yf_record_files`; update `vtiger_users.imagename`; write `.base64` sidecar.

Single master PNG — CSS scales (~50px list, ~40px timeline, ~70px header); no separate thumbnail files.

## URL API (never `storage/…` in `<img src>`)

| Use | Method |
|---|---|
| Web URL | `Users\Models\Record::getImageWebUrl()` → `file.php?module=Users&action=Image&record={id}` or default icon |
| Disk path (PHP only) | `getImageRelativePath()` |
| Resolve absolute | `RecordFile::resolveAbsolutePath($relativePath)` |
| Serve handler | `src/Modules/Users/Files/Image.php` |
| uitype 69 / comments / timeline | `$USER_MODEL->getImageWebUrl()` (ModComments delegates to commentor user) |
| PDF/HTML generator | `getUserPhotoImgHtmlForGenerator()` (sidecar data-URI) |

No `getImagePath()` — do not reintroduce.

## Templates

- Left panel: `BodyLeft.tpl` — `getImageRelativePath()` gates `userName--withPhoto`; `<img class="userNamePhoto">` uses `getImageWebUrl()`.
- CSS: `css.mdc` → Left panel header.

## Mail sidecars

Sidecar must hold **PNG/jpeg/gif** data URI (not WebP). Built by `writeUserPhotoBase64SidecarForRelativeImage()`; legacy WebP on disk is converted on write. PHPMailer embed rules: `mail-module.mdc` → Inline images.

## Diagnose & repair

```sql
SELECT u.id, u.user_name, u.imagename, rf.storage_path
FROM vtiger_users u
LEFT JOIN s_yf_record_files rf ON rf.crm_record_id = u.id AND rf.role = 'image'
WHERE u.id = ?;
```

Missing `rf` but file on disk under `storage/Users/`:

1. `INSERT vtiger_crmentity` (`crmid = id`, `setype = 'Users'`, `smownerid = id`, timestamps) if absent.
2. `INSERT s_yf_record_files` (`role='image'`, `storage_path`, `original_name`, `mime_type='image/png'`, `size_bytes`).
3. `UPDATE vtiger_users SET imagename = …`.
4. Regenerate sidecar if needed: `Record::writeUserPhotoBase64SidecarForRelativeImage($relativePath, 'image/png')`.

Verify: `Record::getInstanceById($id, 'Users')->getImageRelativePath()` non-null; `RecordFile::resolveAbsolutePath()` readable.

General record-file storage (non-Users): `documents-storage.mdc`.
